original_font_information.description: LL Ruder Plakat is designed by Hans-Christian Pulver, Arve Båtevik and Anatole Couteau at Lineto (2018–2021). It is a faithful digital recreation and extension of the wood type font by Emil Ruder, created with his students for use at the print workshop at Allgemeine Gewerbeschule Basel in the mid-1950s. In its variable version, it adds to the original design by extending the typeface’s range beyond the original proportions, mirroring the distinctive styles popular in Swiss graphic design of the era. First released by Lineto in 2022. Font engineering and mastering by Alphabet Type GmbH.
